    "# Step 3: LLM Generation with Citation-Grounded Responses\n",
    "\n",
    "**Input:** `faiss_index.bin`, `bm25_index.pkl`, `indexed_documents.json`  \n",
    "**Output:** Structured audit responses with traceable citations\n",
    "\n",
    "This step wires the hybrid retriever from Step 2 to Claude. Every claim in the response is grounded in a specific retrieved document — no hallucination, full traceability.\n",
    "\n",
    "We support **three query modes**:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Mode | Description | Example |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `general` | Standard audit Q&A | \"What evidence is needed for access control?\" |\n",
    "| `compliance_check` | Is a control requirement met? | \"Does ITGC cover risk assessment?\" |\n",
    "| `cross_mapping` | Map ITGC ↔ ISO 27001 controls | \"How does ITGC change management map to ISO 27001?\" |"
   ]
